# Vulppi React Hooks

## Installation

```bash
npm install @vulppi/react-hooks
```

## Usage

```tsx
import { useTimer } from '@vulppi/react-hooks'

const Component = () => {
  const [time, { start, stop, restart }] = useTimer()

  return (
    <div>
      <div>{time}</div>
      <button onClick={start}>Start</button>
      <button onClick={stop}>Stop</button>
      <button onClick={restart}>Restart</button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Hooks table

| Hook                                                       | Description                                      |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| [useBoolean](./src/use-boolean/README.md)                  | A hook to create and control a boolean.          |
| [useClickOutside](./src/use-click-outside/README.md)       | A hook to detect click outside of an element.    |
| [useDebounce](./src/use-debounce/README.md)                | A hook to debounce a function.                   |
| [useDebounceTrigger](./src/use-debounce-trigger/README.md) | A hook to debounce before triggering a function. |
| [useInterval](./src/use-interval/README.md)                | A hook to create and control an interval.        |
| [useIsMounted](./src/use-is-mounted/README.md)             | A hook to check if component is mounted.         |
| [useMediaQuery](./src/use-media-query/README.md)           | A hook to check if media query matches.          |
| [useMergeRef](./src/use-merge-ref/README.md)               | A hook to merge multiple refs.                   |
| [useRerender](./src/use-rerender/README.md)                | A hook to force component to rerender.           |
| [useStateDebounce](./src/use-state-debounce/README.md)     | A hook to debounce a state.                      |
| [useTimeout](./src/use-timeout/README.md)                  | A hook to call function after a timeout.         |
| [useTimer](./src/use-timer/README.md)                      | A hook to create and control a timer.            |

